This course introduces the fundamentals of research process and teaches to differentiate between qualitative and quantitative research approach. Course gives an overview of the main data gathering and analysis methods in social sciences. Specifically, the course will introduce the principles of conducting interviews, questionnaires, observations and document analysis, together with the data analysis.Objectives/eesmärkid:  This course enables to develop an understanding of research methodology, but also to  gain knowledge of different qualitative and quantitative research and analysis methods used in social sciences, and  specifically, at student's own field of study.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) has knowledges on how to draft a literature review; 2) has basic knowledge of different data gathering and analysing methods, together with research methodologies; 3) has skills to apply some data gathering methods (interviews, observations, document analysis); 4) has skills to carry out basic data analysis and to interpret and generalise the results of data analysis and to present the research results; 5) has skills to find necessary instructions for (scientific) research.
